Feature: Deprecated verification_status field is not returned in API responses

  As an integrator building on the Kira API
  I want the API to only return current, non-deprecated fields
  So that I don't accidentally build on fields that will be removed

  Background:
    Given I have a valid Bearer token from POST /auth
    And I set required auth headers

  Scenario: User creation response contains deprecated verification_status field
    When I POST to /v1/users with a valid user payload
    Then the response status should be 201
    And the response body contains "status": "CREATED"
    And the response body also contains "verification_status": "unverified"
    But the documentation states "verification_status is deprecated — use status instead"
    And both fields are present simultaneously with equivalent but differently-named values

  Scenario: Deprecated field should not appear in responses or should include deprecation warning
    When I POST to /v1/users with a valid user payload
    Then either:
      - "verification_status" should not appear in the response body, OR
      - "verification_status" should include a deprecation header or inline warning
    But currently it appears with no indication that it will be removed

  Scenario: Integrator builds flow using verification_status and experiences silent breakage
    Given an integrator reads the user creation response and sees "verification_status": "unverified"
    And they build their KYC polling logic on "verification_status"
    When Kira removes the deprecated field in a future API version
    Then the integrator's polling logic will silently stop working
    And no webhook or changelog entry will alert them because the field was already marked deprecated
